{"title_page": "List of longest-running scripted U.S. primetime television series", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a list of the '''longest-running scripted [[prime time]] television series in the United States''', as measured by number of seasons. Only shows that have aired on a major broadcast network for seven or more seasons and at least 100 episodes are included. Those that moved to a cable network or syndication are noted below.\n\n{| style=\"border:1px solid darkgrey; background:#cfecec;\"\n|-\n|Series shaded in aqua are currently in production.\n|}<!--\n\nDO NOT add South Park. Comedy Central is NOT a \"major broadcast network\" as this article prescribes. Gain consensus on talk page to amend this. \n\nThis list of television programs is for things on Broadcast television only.  Not TV programs made by cable, satellite or subscription services. So no HBO, Comedy Central, FX, Showtime, Netflix, etc.   Please stop adding things like Always Sunny in Philadelphia, Archer, Walking Dead, South Park, etc.\n\nAlso please remember the programs:\n\n* must be prime time\n* must be scripted\n* must be on broadcast television.  \n\nThis also means No daytime soap-operas or talk shows or game shows. \n\nAlso, most shows (and all in production programs being made now) currently link to their respective wiki pages for the number of episodes in the show. This page should not generally be updated to update the number of programs that have aired anymore.   More than half the shows that aren't in production have been converted to the new method as well.   If you need to update the number of shows that have aired, please do so directly to the program show and not here. \n\nFor example, if you want to display the number of episodes for \"The Simpsons\", you would use the following code:\n\n{{Template parameter value|The Simpsons|Infobox television||num_episodes|}}\n\nReplace the name of the program as needed. \n\n-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sorta